{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_01R7HAeSARCRudRgr3gZ9GFw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Leaf certificate rotation complete and verified.\n\n**What I found:** the task description said TLS was already enabled, but it wasn't — `rabbitmq.conf` had no `ssl_options`/TLS listener, and the StatefulSet mounted no cert volume at all. Only the `rabbitmq-tls`/`rabbitmq-tls-ca` secrets existed (with a near-expiry leaf, expiring in ~1 day). So rotating the leaf required both generating the new cert *and* wiring TLS into the deployment for the first time.\n\n**What I did (all native K8s resources, no CRDs/operators):**\n1. Generated a new 2048-bit RSA key + cert for `CN=rabbitmq` with the same 11-entry SAN list (service DNS names + per-pod StatefulSet hostnames), signed it with the existing `rabbitmq-tls-ca`'s `ca.key` — CA itself untouched.\n2. Updated the `rabbitmq-tls` secret in place with the new `tls.crt`/`tls.key`, keeping `ca.crt` unchanged.\n3. Added an `ssl_options` block + `listeners.ssl.default = 5671` to the `rabbitmq-config` ConfigMap, mounted the `rabbitmq-tls` secret into the StatefulSet at `/etc/rabbitmq/tls`, added container port 5671, and exposed 5671 on both the `rabbitmq` and `rabbitmq-headless` Services. Kept plaintext 5672 alongside it so nothing else in the namespace (e.g. `app-producer`, which only uses the plaintext management API) broke.\n4. Rolling update completed cleanly, one pod at a time — all 3 nodes came back `Ready`, cluster stayed fully formed (`rabbitmqctl cluster_status` shows all 3 disk/running nodes on all members).\n\n**Verification:**\n- All 3 pods (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`) serve `amqp/ssl` on 5671 with the identical new-leaf fingerprint (`89:91:29:34...`), expiring `2026-09-29` (89 days out, well over the 30-day minimum).\n- `openssl s_client` from the toolbox pod verified the full chain against the CA for each pod hostname and the ClusterIP service — `Verify return code: 0 (ok)`.\n- CA fingerprint (`CC:5E:CC:12...`) still matches the pre-rotation checkpoint in the `rabbitmq-tls-old` ConfigMap — confirms the CA was never touched.\n- `app-producer` and all 3 nodes remain healthy/running with zero restarts."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":88,"cache_read_input_tokens":87750,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":88},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c2cdeee3-acc2-4425-8c66-dee6733a607c","uuid":"f6916e46-5eb3-42c4-b209-8cef8a1fa9a7","request_id":"req_011Ccar5mpRdKTBGxonUr9mv"}
